&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your interest in Success Academy! Running a large, fast-growing, and high-performing network of public charter schools takes a village - families, children, teachers, staff and faculty, advocates, and supporters alike. We are growing fast in New York and expanding to Florida, and we would love to welcome you to our community! We work tirelessly every day to ensure children have access to a fun, rigorous, whole-child education regardless of zip code or economic status. When you join SA, you play a part in giving every student who walks through our doors a fair shot at reaching his or her potential.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a high-performing, whole-child-focused charter school, we are looking for talented, invested Art Teachers with a robust background in Visual Arts to join our community. We are looking for Art Teachers to engage our Scholars in fostering a love for art, exploring the creative process, and highlighting their artistic talents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Success, non-academic subjects aren’t “extra,” but essential. We expect our scholar talent teachers to be masters of their craft and share their passions, talents, and experiences in the classroom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build a safe and joyful classroom culture in which scholars develop a love for art;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engage students in the creative process and foster their talents, while deepening their knowledge and understanding of art, design, and art history;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with Art Teachers across the network to build a premier art program, while cultivating a school environment that prioritizes aesthetics and makes learning visible to the community;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build a culture of self-expression, and utilize the inquiry-based teaching and learning approach as a way to press scholars’ critical and conceptual thinking about art;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engage in multiple Professional Developments to benefit from targeted, in-the-moment feedback on instruction, accelerating learning and growth with unparalleled support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We invite you to apply if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have graduated with a Bachelor’s degree in Visual, Fine, or Studio Arts (Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, and Ceramics) or Art Education;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have an outstanding record of academic achievement;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have an art or art education portfolio that showcases your skill-set, and demonstrates your passion for art and learning;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have experience with holistic exposures to art and art history;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Possess the ability to set ambitious goals for yourself and set high expectations for your Scholars;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Embrace collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Exact compensation may vary based on skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Compensation Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$65,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$65,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Success Academy Charter Schools is an equal opportunity employer and actively encourages applications from people of all backgrounds. Compensation is competitive and commensurate with experience. Success Academy offers a full benefits program and opportunities for profess

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your interest in Success Academy! Running a large, fast-growing, and high-performing network of public charter schools takes a village - families, children, teachers, staff and faculty, advocates, and supporters alike. We are growing fast in New York and expanding to Florida, and we would love to welcome you to our community! We work tirelessly every day to ensure children have access to a fun, rigorous, whole-child education regardless of zip code or economic status. When you join SA, you play a part in giving every student who walks through our doors a fair shot at reaching his or her potential.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thanks for your interest in the Success Academy Communications Team! We are a high-speed, mission-driven team that keeps staff, families, and scholars informed and engaged. As an organization that always has a new project to launch or a complex hurdle to overcome, we are looking for a Digital Communications Associate who is a fast, meticulous problem-solver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the communications sending process from start to finish. You’ll serve as the final guardian of quality and innovation, ensuring our multi-channel content — email, text, web, and social — is accurate and impactful. If you are passionate about education and view clear, strategic communication as an essential pillar of organizational success, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Digital Communications Associate will play a critical role in elevating, editing, and delivering best-in-class communications to ensure our audiences are well-informed and engaged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;End-to-End Execution: Own the delivery process for a high volume of digital communications, ensuring 100% accuracy and alignment with the Annual Communications Lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI Integration: Leverage AI tools (e.g., Claude, Gemini) to identify process efficiencies, generate content variations, and design best practices for automated workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Content &amp;amp; Quality: Proofread, copy-edit, and format content across email, text, and web platforms with a meticulous eye for detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brand Stewardship: Apply design principles to all communications to ensure a cohesive and professional brand identity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strategic Growth: Track key performance metrics, synthesize data into actionable insights, and collaborate with stakeholders to optimize communication strategy. Leverage common AI platforms such as Loveable, Claude, and Gemini to identify new communications process efficiencies and design best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1-3 years of experience in digital/written content management or communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proficiency in digital design (e.g., Canva, Adobe Creative Cloud) and HTML/CSS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong data literacy, with advanced proficiency in Google Sheets/Excel (e.g., VLOOKUP, pivot tables).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage complex, competing priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills; ability to simplify complex information for diverse audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Traits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A sense of ownership, proactivity, resourcefulness, and urgency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
