&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a creative and results-driven &lt;strong&gt;Wellness &amp;amp; Movement Coach&lt;/strong&gt; who excels at transforming small spaces into high-energy hubs of physical development. In this role, you will adapt traditional athletic concepts for a classroom setting, ensuring scholars remain active, challenged, and engaged regardless of the square footage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovate in Small Spaces:&lt;/strong&gt; Adapt and deliver physical activity sessions, including yoga, calisthenics, and flexibility training, tailored specifically for classroom environments and limited-space settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Be part of a highly motivated team committed to education reform and the building of exemplary schools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate: &lt;/strong&gt;With coaches across the network to develop a world-class wellness program that prioritizes scholar health and kinesthetic awareness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inspire:&lt;/strong&gt; Cultivate a love for movement and healthy living, encouraging critical thinking through instruction that connects physical discipline to academic focus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate and lead family meetings to promote wellness habits at home.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow:&lt;/strong&gt; Receive routine, ongoing feedback and professional development from an outstanding leadership team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We invite you to apply if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience coaching youth in &lt;strong&gt;specialized movement disciplines&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., yoga, dance, martial arts, strength and conditioning, SAQ, or gymnastics).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess the &lt;strong&gt;spatial creativity&lt;/strong&gt; to lead engaging, safe, and high-intensity activities within a classroom or small-room footprint.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are able to develop and teach concepts such as &lt;strong&gt;mindfulness, body mechanics, healthy lifestyles, and perseverance&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a demonstrated track record of propelling students’ understanding of physical fitness and self-regulation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have an advanced understanding of one or more of the following:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yoga &amp;amp; Mindfulness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Static Strength &amp;amp; Isometric Training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mobility &amp;amp; Stretching Protocols&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Low-Impact Aerobics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience working with &lt;strong&gt;K-4 grades&lt;/strong&gt;

